## Overview

[EXCERPT:Overview]
The **Toolbar** is displayed along the top of the Persona interface window by default. It contains a variety of common functions you will need when editing animation assets.
[/EXCERPT:Overview]

[REGION:tip]
If you do not see the Toolbar, you can show it using the **Window** menu within Persona.
[/REGION]

## Toolbar Modes

As you may know, Persona has four different _modes_ that it uses to selectively display aspects of its interface based on what the user is currently doing. This also means that the common commands you will use within Persona will change along with the modes. The Toolbar intuitively updates to hide away any commands that would not be useful in the current mode. For instance:

When in **Skeleton**, **Mesh**, or **Animation** modes, the Toolbar will look something like this:


![](Toolbar_01.png)

 However, when in **Graph** mode, the toolbar expands with further features, looking like this:

![](Toolbar_2.png)

You may notice that many of the additional buttons are the same as those used in the Blueprint Editor window. 


